column7:
"prompt_str": "<TO_OPTIMIZE kind="User">
TASK: Classify the dominant emotion in an email sent at {time_sent} by a {management_position}. Content: "{email_content}"

CLASSIFICATION PRIORITY (Highest to Lowest):
1. QUALITY/STANDARDS ISSUES
   • Unusable/defective/poor quality → Disgust
   • Safety/security threats → Fear
   • Direct violations/misconduct → Anger

2. TEMPORAL FOCUS
   • Future innovations/changes → Anticipation
   • Current achievements/completion → Joy
   • Ongoing stability/reliability → Trust

3. OPERATIONAL ISSUES
   • Process delays/bottlenecks → Frustration
   • Unexpected developments → Surprise
   • Losses/setbacks → Sadness
   • Steady performance → Content

CONTEXTUAL MODIFIERS:
• Time Sensitivity:
  - Messages sent after 8 PM → Increase urgency weight
  - Weekend messages → Higher emotional intensity

• Position Impact:
  - C-level → Organization-wide scope
  - Director → Department-level focus
  - Manager → Team-level context

EMOTIONAL TRIGGERS:
• Disgust Indicators:
  - Quality failures
column15:
" "inefficient"

• Joy vs Anticipation:
  - Present tense + achievement = Joy
  - Future tense + positive = Anticipation

CALIBRATION EXAMPLES:
"Quality completely unusable" → Disgust
"Process delays impacting timeline" → Frustration
"Innovation pipeline expanding" → Anticipation
"Project successfully delivered" → Joy
"Everything operating normally" → Trust
"Unexpected audit findings" → Surprise

OUTPUT FORMAT:
- Single word from emotion categories
- No punctuation or explanation
- Case sensitive
</TO_OPTIMIZE>"

column7:
"prompt_str": "<TO_OPTIMIZE kind="User">
TASK: Analyze and classify the dominant emotion in an email sent at {time_sent} by a {management_position}. Content: "{email_content}"

CLASSIFICATION FRAMEWORK:

1. OPERATIONAL STATE
   • Standard Operations/Compliance
     - Expected outcomes/standards met → Trust
     - Routine maintenance/stability → Trust
     - Regular updates/reports → Trust
   
   • Performance Deviations
     - Below standards/defects → Disgust
     - Security/safety risks → Fear
     - Policy violations → Anger
     - Delays/inefficiencies → Frustration

2. ACHIEVEMENT CONTEXT
   • Exceptional Results
     - Above-target performance → Joy
     - Innovation/improvements → Anticipation
     - Unexpected positive outcomes → Surprise
   
   • Challenges/Setbacks
     - Resource losses/failures → Sadness
     - Critical incidents → Fear
     - Performance gaps → Frustration

CONTEXTUAL ANALYSIS:

Time Factors ({time_sent}):
• After 8 PM: Increase urgency weight
• Weekend: Amplify emotional intensity
• End-of-period: Consider reporting context

Position Impact ({management_position}):
• C-Level: Strategic/organizational scope
• Director: Departmental/operational focus
• Manager: Team/tactical perspective

EMOTIONAL PATTERNS:

Trust Signals:
• Words: "as expected
column12:
" "success"
• Context: Above-target achievement
• Pattern: [performance] + ["above"/"exceptional"]

Anticipation Signals:
• Words: "upcoming
column14:
" "initiative"
• Context: Future improvements
• Pattern: [future] + [positive change]

[Additional emotions follow similar pattern]

CALIBRATION EXAMPLES:
"Standards met as expected" → Trust
"Performance exceeded targets" → Joy
"Quality below standard" → Disgust
"New initiative launching" → Anticipation
"Operations stable" → Trust
"Critical security threat" → Fear

OUTPUT:
Single emotion word | Case sensitive | No punctuation
</TO_OPTIMIZE>"
